html
    head
        title Image search abstraction layer
        link(
            rel='stylesheet'
            href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/twitter-bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css'
        )
    body
        div(class='container')
            div(class='jumbotron')
                h1 Image search abstraction layer
        
            blockquote
                h2 User stories :
                p 1) I can get the image URLs, alt text and page urls for a set of images relating to a given search string
                p 2) I can paginate through the responses by adding a ?offset=2 parameter to the URL 
                p 3) I can get a list of the most recently submitted search strings
                    
            h2 Example :
            p I can search for images of grumpy cat:
            code  https://cryptic-ridge-9197.herokuapp.com/api/imagesearch/grumpy%20cat?offset=10
            br
            br
            p and the app will return a JSON array of images of gumpy cat
            br
            p when I log onto :
            code https://cryptic-ridge-9197.herokuapp.com/api/latest/imagesearch/
            br
            br
            p I can browse through previous queries which have been saved in the database
            br
            br
            p the databse is on mlab and the images come from Imgur API